@@TJvArrowButton.Spacing
Summary
  Indicates the position of the image and the caption.
Description
  Spacing specifies the number of pixels between the caption and the image. It works exactly like
  TSpeedButton.Spacing.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.PressBoth
Summary
  Specifies if both the button and the arrow should be pressed simultaneously.
Description
  PressBoth indicates whether or not both the button as well as the arrow should be pressed when one
  of the two is clicked. By default this property is set to True.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Layout
Summary
  Specifies the location of the image and caption.
Description
  Layout specifies where the image and caption are rendered on the button. See TSpeedButton.Layout
  for more information.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.NumGlyphs
Summary
  The number of images in the Glyph property.
Description
  NumGlyphs indicate the number of images the Glyph property holds. NumGlyphs works just like
  TSpeedButton.NumGlyphs.
See Also
  TJvArrowButton.Glyph

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.OnDrop
Summary
  Occurs when the user clicks the arrow.
Description
  Write an OnDrop event to perform special tasks when the user presses the arrow of the button. If a
  DropDown menu is assigned, it will be displayed, regardless if an OnDrop handler is assigned.
See Also
  TJvArrowButton.DropDown

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Margin
Summary
  Space between the border and the image/caption.
Description
  Margin specifies the number of pixels between the button edge and the image or caption. Margin
  works exactly like TSpeedButton.Margin.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.GroupIndex
Summary
  Index of the group this button belongs to.
Description
  GroupIndex holds the index of the group this button is part of. This can be used to simulate radio
  buttons using a group of arrow buttons.
  
  When the group index of buttons are equal and set to a value <> 0, only 1 button of that group is
  allowed to be left in the down state. Clicking on another button will set that button to the down
  state and release any other button that might be in the down state.
See Also
  TJvArrowButton.AllowAllUp

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvArrowButton.Glyph
Summary
  The image to show on the button.
Description
  Glyph can be set to a bitmap object containing the image to show on the button. The bitmap can
  contain up to 4 images following the same rules as TSpeedButton.Glyph.
See Also
  TJvArrowButton.NumGlyphs

